  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(9) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "And the Lord",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (Jehovah) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "spake unto Gad.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—Samuel, “And David arose in the morning. Now a word of Jehovah had come to Gad the prophet, a seer of David, saying—“ This appears to be more original than our text.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "David’s seer.—Better, a seer of David’s, for the same title is applied to Heman (1Chronicles 25:5). For Gad, see 1Samuel 22:5, and 1Chronicles 29:29. From the latter passage it has been inferred that it was Gad who wrote the original record of the census.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "David’s seer.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Better, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "a seer of David’s,",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " for the same title is applied to Heman (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Chronicles 25:5",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "). For Gad, see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Samuel 22:5",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", and ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Chronicles 29:29",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". From the latter passage it has been inferred that it was Gad who wrote the original record of the census.",
            "children": []
